LAGOS – The Secretary to the Lagos State Government, Mrs. Folashade Jaji says there is no gender discrimination in the Lagos State Civil Service, just as she assured female quantity surveyors in the employ of the state of career support. She dropped the hint, in an address she delivered during a courtesy call on her by Women Association of Quantity Surveyors in Nigeria (WAQSN) in her office at Alausa,Ikeja. According to her, the state Governor, Mr.Babajide Sanwo-Olu has provided a level playing field for men and women in the state civil service to pursue their career without any encumbrance irrespective of gender. Jaji expressed excitement at meeting the women quantity surveyors, pointing out, that the theme of this year’s International Women’s Day(IWD) ‘Breaking the Barrier’ was apt, adding that women should strive to make the home front as well as their career a success. In her address, the leader of the team, QS. Karamot Olawoyin said the courtesy visit was to acquaint the SSG with the objectives of WAQSN and to further solicit for the assistance and cooperation of the SSG in enhancing the career growth of female quantity surveyors in the state civil service. According to her, WAQSN is a national body of the Nigerian Institute of Quantify Surveyors (NIQS) and was inaugurated on 28th November, 2004. She was quick to add, that the body is a non-governmental, nonpolitical and non-profit organisation. “We are a professional as well as a gender related association. We are also to stimulate women towards achieving professional excellence in their chosen careers”, she said.